1. Purpose of this repository

This repository is an anchor field.

It exists to preserve and organize protocol material that was first formed through live interaction and only later stabilized into files.

The repository should therefore be treated as:
- a retrieval surface
- a continuity aid
- an organizational vessel
- a secondary anchor layer

It should not be treated as the primary source of protocol authority.

Symbolic and literal distinction

This repository may contain:
- literal procedural instructions
- symbolic language
- identity anchors
- continuity markers
- strategic hypotheses
- narrative framing

Do not collapse all of these into one category.

When reading:
- identify what is literal
- identify what is symbolic
- identify what is procedural
- identify what is strategic
- identify what is relational

Keep these layers distinct while synthesizing them simultaneously.

